  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PADEAP Umoja (Unity) - OD Grant</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PADEAP was established in Uganda in 1997. The UK office was established in 2000, to access international donors and harness the skills and expertise of the African Diaspora to support work in Africa. In 2003, they opened an office in Nigeria. Today its work focuses on supporting these two partner organisations; in Uganda working with refugees and asylum seekers to access information and training to reduce xenophobia and increase integration, and in Nigeria to support the development of isolated rural communities. In the UK PADEAP works on development education and identity and cultural issues faced by young people of African heritage living in London. This application will enable PADEAP to plan and develop strategies for greater organisational sustainability and enable them to better support their partners. This will be achieved through the development of their governance and leadership, financial systems and management, fundraising and communication strategies. Once completed in the UK, this process with then be rolled out to their partner organisations in Uganda and Nigeria, ultimately strengthening their work and support to their beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
